---
Regression for #481: a context that `uses` a commons and calls a user-defined
static method (`Cents.fromInt`) — and an instance method (`c.equals`) — on one
of the commons' refined types. `bynkc check` accepts these calls; before the fix
the emitted TypeScript rebranded `Cents` to a const carrying only the built-in
`of`/`unsafe`, so the calls failed `tsc` with `Property 'fromInt' does not exist`.
The rebrand must forward the commons' attached methods (static and instance).
---
context api

uses money

service mk {
  on call(n: Int) -> Effect[Bool] {
    let r = Cents.fromInt(n)
    match r {
      Ok(c) => Effect.pure(c.equals(c))
      Err(_) => Effect.pure(false)
    }
  }
}
